comment.narrative:
No comprehensive legislative act has been adopted by authorities on Persons with Disabilities including on  women and young people with disabilities;
Legislation on accessible environment and accessibility of information not in line with international standards;
National Human Rights Strategy 2014 – 2020 covers policy on PwD;
55 organizations work on rights of PwDs however the focus of their activities is not monitoring of CRPD implementation or social issues;
SSA job coaches and local self governments have low capacity to promote employment of PwDs;
LSG PwD councils have low capacity;
Limited data on awareness on obligations of employers for providing social protection schemes of PwD employees 
No community centers for PwDs existing in Georgia;
No national capacity to provide disability friendly SRHR and GBV services for women and young persons with disabilities;
Limited data available on quality of services delivery to PwDs in selected municipalities;

1.1. Regulations on accessibility approved; Draft National Human Rights Strategy with relevant chapter on disability developed and submitted to the Parliament
1.2.4. Reports on implementation of CRPD prepared by local CSOs/OPDs
1.3.1. All job coaches assigned to employment of PwDs are trained and have the capacity to facilitate employment of PwDs   
Relevant business organizations conduct relevant trainings; At least 1 community center established in Georgia, including in Abkhazia providing social protection and employment opportunities for PwDs;
2.2. At least 70% of activities for the reporting year implemented by target municipalities;
2.2.3. At least 90% of PwDs in the selected municipalities have access to introduced services

1.1. Draft regulations on accessibility developed through an inclusive and participatory process;
1.2.4. At least 30 representatives of women’s CSOs and CBOs capacitated to advocate and monitor implementation of the rights of women with disabilities;
1.3.1. Needs of SSA identified and recommendations developed on capacity building; 
Training module developed for private and public employers on obligations of employers for providing social protection schemes of PwD employees;
2.2. At least 1 community centre established in Georgia, including in Abkhazia providing social protection and employment opportunities for PwDs;
National service provision guiding documents on SRHR and GBV developed;
2.2.3. Regulatory framework (instructions, rules of procedure, etc.) developed and adopted for delivering of at least 2 new services to PwDs in selected municipalities;
Capacity of local municipalities strengthened to deliver social services.

1.1. UNDP supported elaboration of draft of National Human Rights Strategy, the Law on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (LRPD) and draft of guidelines on National Accessibility Plan. In 2020 National Accessibility Standards were also approved. The LRPD was approved by the Parliament.
1.2.4. UNDP built the capacity of OPDs, and NGOs working on the rights of PwDs in the regions of Georgia on the issues of grant proposal writing, project management and reporting. In total, representatives of 18 organizations underwent the training;
1.3.1. UNDP supported the State Employment Agency to review and improve the job description of job coaches for PwDs. Build the capacity of job coaches in the main principals of job coaching for PwDs and communication methods with persons with different types of disabilities. UNDP elaborated the concept of Social Inclusion Centers and issued grant to support piloting of the concept in Ambrolauri, Georgia. The main function of the Centers will be provision of space for social activities and professional skills development. UNDP issued the grant to support building of rehabilitation center for children with Disabilities in Abkhazia, Georgia.
2.2. UNDP engaged national expert for developing Strategy and Action Plan on Social Services to PwDs in selected municipalities. Preliminary meetings were conducted. Due to the resurgence of COVID-19 cases in Georgia and Parliamentary elections in October it was impossible for the national expert to conduct extended meetings and visits in the municipalities;
2.2.3. UNDP engaged national expert for developing Strategy and Action Plan on Social Services to PwDs in selected municipalities. Preliminary meetings were conducted. Due to the resurgence of COVID-19 cases in Georgia and Parliamentary elections in October it was impossible for the national expert to conduct extended meetings and visits in the municipalities
